Even when prefixes are added to the turtle it interprets them incorrectly. In addition it is not able

implement bindings that will improve the situation.

This should fix #205 and should be fixed by running
serve with the --interactive flag.

If serve is not run with interactive flag it does not respond
well to ANY signals that the parent process sends. I think that
serve is fundamentally broken without --interactive. It is good
that it runs in a deamon-like mode but is totally unresponsive in
a way in which normal daemon-like applications shouldn't.

Fix very slow query when using ./terminusdb list with many dbs
COMMIT_TEXT:
I created 388 DBs and it took 90 seconds to list them. But when I
fix this query, it takes around 6 seconds. The reason is that the
original query is very slow because it does not take account that
Db_Uri could be ground already.
Fix very slow query when using ./terminusdb list with many dbs

Increased performance further. If the account requesting the list
is the super_user/admin, there is no need to get the user object
and query the organization of *every* database.

However, even when a specific user wants a list of their DBs
it is also faster now. Since the name of the database is already
in the user object itself, it does not need to be queried.
This saves addiontal time and also removes the need for the
ground check of the DB URI.

Time went from:
./terminusdb list  6.30s user 1.87s system 103% cpu 7.912 total

To:
./terminusdb list  2.37s user 1.21s system 107% cpu 3.316 total

COMMIT_HEADLINE: Fix admin not having access to other databases (#307)
COMMIT_TEXT:
The permission checking was too strict. If any other use makes a
DB, the admin does not have write access. Now it checks whether
you are actually admin.

The organization filter was too strict. If the organization
name contained one of the excluded names, it would already
forbid this organization too exist. Even a organization name
called "soundboard" would be forbidden by the existing filter.

Now it only checks whether the whole name is the forbidden word.
The exception to this rule is the | (pipe) character which
should always be forbidden.
